The paper deals with the problem of indexing a text to efficiently answer queries for non-overlapping occurrences of a pattern within a given range. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), computational complexity (cs.CC), and data mining (cs.DM). However, given the focus on indexing and querying large amounts of text data, we believe that cs.DS and cs.IR are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DB, cs.CC, and cs.DM.
